						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In the end the only thing that seems to work properly is to avoid faking colors altogether and try to make graphics look good exclusively with solid colors, but that starts getting annoying when the amount of colors is so small.</div><br />You work with what you got, and what you've got is a console developed during the early-to-mid-80s and RTM mid-to-late 80s, using technology that was available at the time.  I dunno what else there is to say; that's the reality of the situation.  If you absolutely need/want more colours to accomplish the visual style you want, I would recommend going the SNES/SFC route.  You'll be surprised how much easier it is to develop on the that platform anyway.</div>

